      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOUGH CALL (4) last start finished 4th in a Maiden on March 12 over 300m at Casino behind Summer Bay beaten 6 lengths (17.44). Looks hard to beat with even luck. SHE'S A ANGEL (1) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 0.8 lengths second (17.69) in a Maiden at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Expecting significant improvement this line-up. NOT SO SAVAGE (3) settled close to the lead but checked in the run and turned spotting a start, missing the frame when fourth (17.93) at this track over 300m in a Maiden. Good beginner and aided by a handy draw. May be worth another try. PEPPA LANE (2) is an improver in the mix despite missing out at this track when making debut.",
